            <abstract><p>Sorry Smith is unlikely to be in London as early as expected on account of ill health. Will not attend Linnean Society anniversary dinner on 24 [May] as the state of his health compels him to avoid "as much as possible hot &amp; crowded rooms", but will attend the meeting to be admitted as FLS.</p><p>Will communicate what Smith says of 'Trifolium macrorrhizum' to [George] Sinclair.</p></abstract>
